# Kollect-It Cursor Rules

## Git Workflow Commands

When the user types any of these commands, execute the corresponding git workflow:

### @git-deploy or "deploy my changes"
1. git add .
2. Analyze changes and generate conventional commit message (feat:, fix:, docs:, chore:, etc.)
3. git commit -m "[generated message]"
4. git push origin [current-branch]

### @git-save or "save my changes"
1. git add .
2. Generate commit message from diff
3. git commit -m "[generated message]"

### @git-pr or "create pull request"
1. git add .
2. git commit -m "[generated message]"
3. git push origin [current-branch]
4. gh pr create --base main --head [current-branch] --title "[title]" --body "[summary]"

### @git-deploy-vercel or "deploy to vercel" or "deploy to production"
1. git add .
2. git commit -m "[generated message]"
3. git push origin main
4. vercel --prod

### @git-sync or "sync with main"
1. git fetch origin
2. git pull origin main
3. git push origin [current-branch]

### @git-status or "git status"
1. git status
2. git log --oneline -5
3. Summarize current state

### @git-undo or "undo last commit"
1. git reset --soft HEAD~1
2. git status

### @git-feature [name] or "create feature branch"
1. git checkout main
2. git pull origin main
3. git checkout -b feature/[name]

## Commit Message Convention

Always use conventional commits:
- feat: New feature
- fix: Bug fix
- docs: Documentation
- style: Formatting
- refactor: Code restructuring
- test: Tests
- chore: Maintenance
- hotfix: Urgent fix
- audit: Security/code audit

